Yes, you can absolutely show Mermaid charts in Jupyter Notebooks. Jupyter Notebooks (and JupyterLab) have built-in support for rendering Mermaid syntax directly in Markdown cells.

Here's how you do it:

1.  **Create a Markdown cell** in your Jupyter Notebook.
2.  **Use a `mermaid` fenced code block**: Inside the Markdown cell, wrap your Mermaid syntax with ````mermaid` and ````.

For example:

````markdown
```mermaid
graph TD;
    A-->B;
    A-->C;
    B-->D;
    C-->D;
```
````

When you run (or render) that Markdown cell, Jupyter will interpret the `mermaid` block and display the diagram. You don't need any special extensions or installations for this to work in modern Jupyter environments.

